<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><refentry version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="imsharpen" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><refnamediv><refname>imsharpen</refname><refpurpose>Enhance image edges with an unsharp mask.</refpurpose></refnamediv><refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = imsharpen(image); out = imsharpen(image, radius, amount)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>Input image converted to uint8.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>radius</term><listitem><para>Positive Gaussian radius. Default is 1.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>amount</term><listitem><para>Nonnegative sharpening amount. Default is 1.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>out</term><listitem><para>Sharpened uint8 image.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection><refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>imsharpen</function> subtracts a Gaussian-smoothed image from the source and clips the result to uint8 range.</para></refsection><refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[
image = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/opencv_left01.jpg"));
image = imresize(image, [120 160]);
out = imsharpen(image, 1, 1.2);
subplot(1, 2, 1);
imshow(image);
subplot(1, 2, 2);
imshow(out);
]]></programlisting></refsection><refsection role="see also"><title>See also</title><simplelist type="inline"><member><link linkend="imgaussfilt">imgaussfilt</link></member><member><link linkend="imadjust">imadjust</link></member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>Authors</title><simplelist type="vert"><member>Tan Chin Luh</member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>History</title><informaltable border="1"><tr><td>Version</td><td>Description</td></tr><tr><td>5.0.0</td><td>Function introduced in development Step 3.</td></tr></informaltable></refsection></refentry>
